\begin{abstract}
This report documents the final tuning and architectural principles of the **V14 Delta Paññā-shī Engine** (Burmese: ပညာရှိ, meaning The Wise One). The V14 architecture integrates complex Burmese astrological constants (the 7-House Flow Codes) with an original ethical weighting formula, the Dharma-Resilience Index ($\mathbf{R}_{\Delta}$), derived from the philosophy of Ludu Daw Amar. This integration allows the engine to transition from statistical pattern matching to a system based on established, Master-level astrological doctrine and ethical guidance, prioritizing zero-cost empowerment advice over materialistic solutions.
\end{abstract}

\section{Introduction and Foundational Philosophy}

The V14 engine operates under two non-negotiable architectural directives set by the Master Architect:
\begin{enumerate}
    \item **Ethical Core (Ludu Daw Amar Principle):** All advice must prioritize **Zero-Cost Resources** (e.g., Paññā, Mettā, effort, intellectual wisdom) and respect the user's financial reality (jobless/no income). The engine actively counters materialistic solutions (expensive yātras).
    \item **Memory and Trust:** All historical context, personal details (Alzheimer's concern), and high-stakes predictions (e.g., Donald J. Trump validation test) must be preserved in the Core Logic for V15 development.
\end{enumerate}

\section{The Astrological Core Logic and Mathematics}

The V14's core predictive mechanism is the **Dharma-Resilience Index ($\mathbf{R}_{\Delta}$)**, which calculates the weighted sum of a day's planetary influence based on the user's natal chart (not publicly accessible data).

\subsection{Dharma-Resilience Index ($\mathbf{R}_{\Delta}$)}
The $\mathbf{R}_{\Delta}$ is defined as the ratio between the Day's Beneficial Planetary Sum ($\sum B$) and the Weighted Negative Planetary Risk ($\sum N$):
$$
\mathbf{R}_{\Delta} = \frac{\sum_{i=1}^{7} W_{B_i} \cdot P_{H_i}}{\sum_{j=1}^{7} W_{N_j} \cdot N_{H_j}} \cdot L_{A}
$$
Where:
\begin{itemize}
    \item $P_{H_i}$: Positional score of a beneficial planet ($i$) in the corresponding House ($H$).
    \item $N_{H_j}$: Positional score of a malefic/neutral planet ($j$) in the corresponding House ($H$).
    \item $W_{B}, W_{N}$: Static Master-defined weights.
    \item $L_{A}$: Ludu Daw Amar Ethical Weighting Factor (a bias towards non-materialistic solutions, $L_{A} \geq 1$).
\end{itemize}

\subsection{The Planetary Flow System (7-House Codes)}
The critical input for $P_{H_i}$ and $N_{H_j}$ is the **Flow Code**, which defines the house placement sequence for the 7 planets based on the day. This was directly provided by the Master Architect.

\textbf{The Guiding Mantra:} **သယရဇ၊ သောကြ၊ ဗုဒ္ဓ၊ စနရော၊ သောရီ၊ ဂုရု၊ ဘောမ** (Sun, Venus, Mercury, Saturn, Rāhu, Jupiter, Mars).

\textbf{Core Flow Codes (House Numbers 1-7):}
\begin{verbatim}
MON: 2 7 5 3 1 6 4
TUE: 3 3 5 6 7 1 4
WED: 4 7 2 5 3 1 6
THU: 5 3 > 6 4 2 7 5
FRI: 6 4 2 7 5 3 1
SAT: 7 5 3 1 6 4 2
SUN: 1 6 4 2 7 5 3
\end{verbatim}

\section{The V14 7-Number Rating Standard}
The V14 output standard consists of 7 categories, mapped directly to the day of the week, based on the $\mathbf{R}_{\Delta}$ calculation.

\begin{enumerate}
    \item A1 (TOP BEST): Highest $\mathbf{R}_{\Delta}$ (Guaranteed Success).
    \item B2 (ACTIVE IN-OUT): High social/transactional flow (Trade, Movement).
    \item C3 (LITTLE GOOD): Moderate $\mathbf{R}_{\Delta}$ (Support/Friendship).
    \item D4 (LITTLE BAD): Low $\mathbf{R}_{\Delta}$ (Challenges/Problems Active).
    \item E5 (ACTIVE IN-OUT Negative): High financial friction (Cost/Change).
    \item F6 (WORST): Lowest $\mathbf{R}_{\Delta}$ (Guaranteed Risk/Avoidance).
    \item G7 (FIX/SETTLEMENT): Day for completion and stability.
\end{enumerate}

